  "prompt": "What is the difference between taper fit, narrow fit, slim fit, regular and straight fit?",
  "response": "Here's a breakdown of different clothing fits:\n\n1. Taper Fit:\n- Narrow at the bottom/leg opening\n- Gradually gets slimmer from thigh to ankle\n- Most fitted around the leg\n- Modern, contemporary style\n\n2. Narrow Fit:\n- Closer to the body\n- Less room around legs and torso\n- Sleek and streamlined\n- Similar to slim fit but potentially even more narrow\n\n3. Slim Fit:\n- Follows body contours more closely\n- Not as tight as skinny fit\n- Provides a more tailored appearance\n- Less fabric/material around body\n\n4. Regular Fit:\n- Standard, traditional cut\n- Comfortable, relaxed space around body\n- Not too tight or too loose\n- Most universal/classic fit\n- Allows more movement\n\n5. Straight Fit:\n- Consistent width from hip to ankle\n- No tapering or significant narrowing\n- Maintains same width throughout leg\n- More traditional, classic style\n- Provides more room and comfort\n\nEach fit serves different body types and style preferences, with variations in how closely they follow body shape and provide room for movement.",
